  "text": "The PCR-RAPD technique identifies dominant markers and thus is considered a di-allelic system in the present study in which only one of two alleles at a locus can be amplified by PCR. Statistical methods developed for analysis of data from codominant markers have been adapted for use with PCR-RAPD markers [CITATION_1] . Electrophoretic patterns were determined by direct comparison between individuals. Each band was analyzed as a binary variant, either present or absent, and then was transcribed to a binary matrix for computational analysis.",
